                  "type": "markdown",
                  "data": {
                    "text": "In algebra, variables (like $x$ or $y$) represent unknown values. They follow the same arithmetic rules as numbers.\n\nExample:\nIf $x = 3$ and $y = 5$:\n\n1. Addition: $x + y = 3 + 5 = 8$\n2. Multiplication: $x \\times y = 3 \\times 5 = 15$\n3. Combined: $2x + 3y = 2(3) + 3(5) = 21$",
