                    "question": "What does $3x + 2x$ simplify to when $x=4$?",
                    "options": [
                      "$5x$ (value: 20)",
                      "$6x$ (value: 24)",
                      "$5x^2$ (value: 80)"
                    ],
                    "correct_answer": 0,
                    "explanation": "Combine like terms: $3x + 2x = 5x$. When $x=4$, $5x = 20$."
                  }
                },
                {
                  "type": "markdown",
                  "data": {
                    "text": "The distributive property connects multiplication and addition:\n\n$a(b + c) = ab + ac$\n\nExample:\n$3(2x + 4) = 6x + 12$\n\nThis works for subtraction too:\n$2(5y - 3) = 10y - 6$",
                    "format": "latex"
